properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 22 at 2:18AM PST until January 22 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Another round of snow this morning into the afternoon. Additional
snow accumulations of 4 to 8 inches through this afternoon.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including the Mount Baker Ski Area.

* WHEN...Until 4 PM PST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow levels will rise steadily later this
afternoon into evening to above 5000 feet by tonight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON ABOVE 3000 FEET
